author: Daniel Greene
description:
Fantasy didn’t start with Tolkien... but it also DID. 
In this video, I trace the history of the modern fantasy genre — from roots in ancient myths and folklore to the pulp magazines, Tolkien’s revolution, and the modern fantasy revolution. From Beowolf and Arthurian legend to Sanderson, Martin, and Le Guin — this is how fantasy became the world’s most ambitious storytelling tradition.
